Hi there. I wanna start sharing more. Thought maybe it be a good idea to do a reintroduction, so here’s 10 things about me based on each of these photos.

1. I love cameras, everything cameras, digital, analog, motion picture, slr’s all of it. I love it so much.
2. I’m addicted to coffee. Straight up addicted. It gets me up in the morning, makes me anxious, and I keep coming back.
3. I’m a walking anime billboard. Almost all my tattoos are references to my favorite anime series out there.
4. I love road tripping. If I could I would live out of my car indefinitely. Maybe one day.
5. I was in an accident in 2021. I almost lost my life it was really scary and it’s put a lot of things into perspective for me.
6. I met Taylor Swift
7. I have a vintage t shirt obsession. It’s insane, I’m almost embarrassed about it as it has gotten totally out of hand lol
8. I love popcorn. A lot. #bandwantspopcorn
9. I have a mini golden doodle named Killua. Yes she is named after an anime character. 
10. The Oregon coast is my second home. Grew up there and will always feel some type of way about it.

I’m really happy to be here. Thank you for following along on my weird journey 

Thanks for supporting me.

The Olympus mju (stylus) Panorama is a fully automatic compact camera that was first produced in 1991.

This model was released in 1992 and is a black and gold special edition that incorporated a panoramic setting that allows the user to switch between a standard 35mm frame and a panoramic one.

Having so much fun with this thing & can not recommend it more. It’s a film summer

Nov 14, 2023 #dayinthelife Today started with a typical editing session. I am working on a couple videos that I shot when I was in NYC with @sonyalpha . Excited to start sharing those with you all. My office is a mess but I kind of like it that way, organized chaos to an extent. The thing I’m doing to my leg is a deep tissue massage. I do it one to two times a day, which helps with swelling and mobility on my right leg. I headed downtown to get wings with some of my favorite people, @jrgonza1ez and @bdorts . If you are ever in Portland you have to check out @fotmpdx . The Fall colors here just keep getting better and better. After wings we headed over to get coffee at @coavacoffee . Stefanie made deconstructed biscuits and gravy for dinner, we watched the @trailblazers game and then wrapped up our night. Thanks for watching today’s video, hope you enjoyed it. See you tomorrow ✌️

At the beginning of 2023, Panic! was heading out to Europe on the last leg of their final tour. Unfortunately I was recovering from surgery & wasn’t able to make it. But @zackcloudhall had sneakily purchased one of my custom disposable cameras & took it out to Europe with him. He had members of the touring party take selfies with the disposable and then shipped it back to me to develop. Although I wasn’t able to be there in person, when I scanned these photos into the computer it made me feel so close to the tour. Some of my favorite photos I developed all last year 🖤
